@Francis

All sets of real numbers is a specific subset of all sets, and all bounded sets is a specific subset of sets of real numbers. So the clue applies to that type of set.

That said, I agree with Paul that ‚Äúend of a set‚Äù is a very poor way to describe a bounded set‚Äôs upper bound. Would not be marked correct in a test in Intro Set Theory.  But it was about par for the course in this particular Saturday puzzle, imo. (And BA and Steve L. would remind us to not, e.g., rely on the medical advice in a Xword clue. Or some analogy like that.)

